  "reviews": "\u201cThis hack-happy Metroidvania's raw energy powers our curiosity\u201d<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://www.myfavouritemagazines.co.uk/gaming/edge-magazine-back-issues/edge-january-2019-issue-327/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Edge Magazine</a><br><br>\u201cRecompile feels just as good as it looks\u201d<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-04-09-recompile-is-a-sci-fi-hacking-platformer-that-makes-hacking-look-beautiful\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Eurogamer</a><br><br>\u201cCertainly one of the best representations of code and neural networks I have seen in a game\u201d<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://www.vg247.com/2019/03/05/recompile-3d-sci-fi-metroidvania-rogue-code/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >VG247</a><br>",
